The paper deals with the complexity of a logic system with team semantics, which is closely related to modal logic and has applications in artificial intelligence and database theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves classification of complexity classes, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another likely category. The use of translations to other logic systems may also suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the satisfiability problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category.
